/* COMPILER/BOOT/iii_main.iii -- iii: THE ORGANISM.  The engine fleet, one body.
 *
 *   iii                      THE FACE: every skill's standing, dues, vitality
 *   iii <skill> [args...]    any engine's whole surface, one level down:
 *                            `iii kardia status`, `iii prove a.iii f b.iii g`,
 *                            `iii ergon census`, `iii motion scroll`, ...
 *   iii whole                the face, explicitly
 *   iii due                  which skills owe a proof on THIS body (pin drift)
 *   iii earn [N]             convert up to N due skills: run each one's own
 *                            self-derivation to its OS-true exit, record PROOF
 *   iii law                  the organism's laws, re-proven this invocation
 *
 * There are no engines here in the old sense.  Nothing is "running" or "not
 * running": every skill has STANDING held in an append-only ledger
 * (STDLIB/build/holos/holos.log), a reach-pin over exactly what its behavior
 * depends on, and activation that is exactly drift or need.  EVERY invocation:
 * (1) the holos self-proof arms run first -- a failed law refuses the face
 * (exit 9, the autognosis pattern); (2) the asked skill executes IN-PROCESS
 * (same argv contract as its retired standalone binary, shifted one seat);
 * (3) the invocation appends a WORK event (skill, pin, exit, seq) -- the
 * organism's autobiography; the exit passes through UNCHANGED.
 *
 * Skill exits are the skill's own.  The organism adds exactly three of its
 * own: 3 usage (unknown skill/verb), 9 SELF-REFUSED (a holos law arm failed),
 * and for `earn`: 1 when a probe reddened.  Requires CWD = the III root for
 * the ledger + pins (a skill still runs elsewhere; the autobiography line is
 * then counted as unwritable, never blocking the skill). */
module iii_main

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn putchar(c: i32) -> i32 from "msvcrt"

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn ho_selfprove() -> u64 from "holos.iii"
